description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an opportunity for a forward thinking and dynamic Junior Clinical Fellow to join the Ophthalmology service based at Rochdale Infirmary and associated sites within the Northern Care Alliance NHS Group. This opportunity is for an enthusiastic and highly motivated clinician to join our active and enthusiastic team of Ophthalmologists, Specialist Nurses, Advanced Practitioners, Technicians and Orthoptists all providing care in the fields of Medical Retina, Oculoplastics, Lacrimal, Cornea, Glaucoma, and Paediatric Ophthalmology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Ophthalmology department is rapidly modernising and expanding service. The successful appointee will be expected to participate in undergraduate and postgraduate teaching and clinical audit, the Trust benefits from close University links.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will contribute to the general Ophthalmology service with outpatient clinics held across multiple sites and assistant surgery in two dedicated eye theatres situated on the Rochdale Infirmary site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participation in the on call rota is essential - banding 1B supplement at 40% of basic salary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates are required to hold full registration with the General Medical Council and a valid licence to practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
